<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3566] Parametrizing H1 and H2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3566</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The DFR normalizations &lt;tt&gt;H1&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;H2&lt;/tt&gt; are parameter-free. This is in line with the &lt;a href=&quot;http://citeseer.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.101.742&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;original article&lt;/a&gt;, but not with the &lt;a href=&quot;http://theses.gla.ac.uk/1570/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;thesis&lt;/a&gt;, where H2 accepts a &lt;tt&gt;c&lt;/tt&gt; parameter, nor with &lt;a href=&quot;http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1835490&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;information-based models&lt;/a&gt;, where H1 also accepts a &lt;tt&gt;c&lt;/tt&gt; parameter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
